data.description:
This spacious, comfortable 3619 sq. ft. home, located in the quiet neighborhood of Lytle Estates, is offered at a reduced price of $290,000. Recent updates include a new master shower  and newly carpeted closets in the master bathroom.  Also eleven (11) NEW "Renewal by Anderson," energy-efficient windows have recently installed (March, 2020).  We spent $36,000 on these windows alone.

The floorplan features an open, inviting entry area, large living room with unique corner fireplace, cozy solarium, generous wet bar area, casual and formal dining areas, large walk-in pantry with appliance outlet, sauna, four bedrooms, two full baths, and laundry area convenient to bedrooms and baths. The third full bath is adjacent to a large game room which can easily be converted into a guest/mother-in-law suite or large efficiency apartment for additional income.  It features an outside entry and option for an interior privacy lock-off.  The space offers three clothes closets, a window seat with storage, as well as a wall storage unit.  
The property has a newly refurbished and painted two-vehicle carport, with attached storage room (also newly constructed, painted and finished out.) 

This beautiful home  offers a newly-landscaped front yard and large newly seeded backyard with new wooden privacy fence along the back property line. A new irrigation system with rain sensor has been installed, as well as a new HVAC condenser with a five-year transferrable warranty. There are 2 HVAC units, and the attic provides foam insulation.
data.whatILove: The floor plan offers wonderful, spacious living areas, with bedrooms located in areas for quiet privacy.  This quiet neighborhood is located near lovely Lytle Lake, and promotes a casual relaxed lifestyle.
